theorem Topology.frontier_subset_closure_compl {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    frontier (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (Aᶜ) := by
  intro x hx
  have hx' : x ∈ closure (A : Set X) \ interior A := by
    simpa [frontier] using hx
  exact (Topology.boundary_subset_closure_compl (A := A)) hx'

theorem Topology.closure_inter_closureCompl_eq_frontier {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    closure (A : Set X) ∩ closure (Aᶜ) = frontier A := by
  classical
  -- We already have an equality expressing this intersection as a difference.
  have h :=
    Topology.closure_inter_closureCompl_eq_closure_diff_interior (A := A)
  -- Rewriting the difference in terms of `frontier` gives the desired result.
  simpa [frontier] using h
